episodes.title: Think again | Scientology - Freedom Remix
episodes.description:
If you think you’ve heard the whole story about Scientology, think again.

CURIOUS ABOUT SCIENTOLOGY? 

You’re not alone. Scientology’s offer of a precise path for bringing about spiritual improvement and a way to accomplish it with absolute certainty comes at a cost of hundreds of thousands of dollars, making it likely the most expensive “religion” ever to exist. Estimates put the current number of Scientologists at around 20-30 thousand worldwide. There are well-designed systems to keep followers in the fold and unquestioning. People who have left the organization have reported numerous abuses including child abuse, elder abuse, human trafficking, kidnapping, and numerous financial crimes.

episodes.title: What is Religious Trauma Syndrome?
episodes.description:
Today I ask Janice What is Religious Trauma Syndrome.

Janice Selbie is a Registered Professional Counsellor and religious trauma recovery consultant. She grew up Pentecostal and became increasingly fundamentalist while married and homeschooling her daughters, aligning her beliefs with the Holdeman Mennonites (calling herself Mennocostal).

Near age 40, Janice's family endured several calamities in a short span, causing her to question her deeply held Christian beliefs. Eventually, she divorce her pastor husband and her religion. Feeling like she had exited a cult, Janice returned to school to study psychology and counselling.
